dcterms:description: Long-tail CIFAR-10 is a modified version of the original CIFAR-10 dataset, which consists of 60,000 32x32 images in 10 classes. The long-tail version was created by sampling long-tail subsets from the original dataset, with an imbalance factor defined as the class size of the largest class divided by the smallest class.
dcterms:title: Long-tail CIFAR-10

dcterms:description: ImageNet-LT is a widely used benchmark dataset for long-tailed recognition, where the sample number of each class is determined by a Pareto distribution. The dataset contains 115.8K images, with the sample number per class ranging from 1280 to 5.
dcterms:title: ImageNet-LT

dcterms:description: Long-tail ImageNet-100 is a sampled dataset from ImageNet-100, where the sample number of each class is determined by a down-sampled Pareto distribution. The dataset contains 12.21K images, with the sample number per class ranging from 1280 to 52.
dcterms:title: Long-tail ImageNet-100
